The Sultan of Sokoto, His Eminence, Sa’ad Abubakar, has advocated for more roles for traditional institutions in the nation’s bid to curtail rising insecurity in the country. Sultan Abubakar wants the old-time tradition restored where traditional institutions played a critical role in the security, administration and management of their community affairs which resulted in the attainment of peaceful coexistence that guaranteed growth and development He disclosed this in his address when he hosted Yoruba Northern Traditional rulers that visited him in his palace in Sokoto. ALSO READ: Funke Akindele, Adesua Etomi, others attend 7th AMVCA nominees and sponsors’ cocktail Canada to no longer pay for Harry and Meghan security Group calls on government to invest in community development Police arrest suspected ritualists in Ondo Pope cancels more official appointments in Italy He stressed the need for respect and understating for one another in a multi-ethnic and religious society like Nigeria. According to him, “This visit of the Northern Yoruba traditional rulers across the northern states is a strong message to divisive agents that are bent at setting the people of Nigeria against one another that the unity of Nigeria has come to stay. “Traditional rulers should be empowered as it was in the past to manage their community in order to guide against security threat that has become a thing of concern to Nigeria as a nation. Earlier, Oba Yusuf Hassan, the Sarkin Yoruba Maiduguri, who is also Chairman, Yoruba Northern Traditional rulers have applauded Sultan Abubakar, for his fatherly roles in sustaining peaceful coexistence among Nigerians. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! HERE IS HOW OVER 5000  NIGERIA MEN HAVE PERMANENTLY OVERCOME TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS RECENT DISCOVERY BY MEDICAL CONSULTANTS LOOK!  YOU DONT NEED TO HAVE ANY EXPERIENCE TO T